{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-2022"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of paints, varnishes and similar coatings, printing ink and mastics"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "2022"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :paint-coatings-ink-mastics/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :consumer-safety :environmental-safety]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :paint-coatings-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae :cfd]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies []
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "PaintAdvisor ⊣ Paint & Coatings Plant Operations Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS COORDINATION
 actor for paints, varnishes and similar coatings, printing ink, and
 mastics manufacturing (pigment-dispersion equipment -- high-speed
 dispersers and bead/ball mills -- plus tinting and filling lines
 producing interior/exterior paints, varnishes, lacquers, primers/
 sealers/undercoats, industrial and marine coatings, offset/
 flexographic/gravure printing ink, and mastics/sealants/caulks) --
 not direct mixing/dispersion-line-equipment control authority. Four
 ops (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Twelve concrete governor checks elaborate this
 blueprint's four HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (no direct mixing/
 dispersion-line-equipment control), permanent line-actuate block,
 independent equipment verification/registration before maintenance
 scheduling, independent batch verification/registration before
 shipment coordination, independent shipment-weight recompute against
 the batch's own logged weight, double-schedule guard, product-type
 validation, viscosity plausibility validation, fineness-of-grind
 (pigment-dispersion-quality) plausibility validation, and VOC
 (volatile organic compound) content regulatory-ceiling validation
 (modeled on the U.S. EPA AIM VOC-content-limit framework and the EU
 Decopaint Directive 2004/42/EC). Safety-concern flagging (chemical-
 hazard solvent-VOC-exposure/flammability/equipment-safety) ALWAYS
 escalates to a human plant supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is the
 only op eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when
 governor-clean."}
